## Overview

`gitproject` is an advanced project creation tool that sets up structured Git projects with dual repository configuration (private organization + public user), comprehensive activity tracking, monorepo support with pnpm, and AI-assisted development features.

### What It Does

- Creates structured project directories with complete development workflow support
- Sets up dual Git repositories (private for organization, public for users)
- Configures monorepo structure with pnpm workspaces
- Generates activity tracking folders for session management
- Creates AI instruction templates and reusable prompts
- Initializes GitHub repositories automatically
- Provides project refactoring capabilities
- Offers project extraction/restoration from GitHub

### Why Use It

- Eliminates manual project setup work
- Enforces consistent project structure across all projects
- Integrates AI development workflow from day one
- Separates private work (activity logs) from public code
- Provides session context preservation
- Automates complex Git repository configuration
- Supports collaborative development patterns
- Enables easy project backup and restoration

---

## Features

- **Dual Repository Setup** - Private org repo + public user repo
- **Monorepo Support** - Full pnpm workspace configuration
- **Activity Tracking** - Comprehensive development session management
- **AI Integration** - Pre-configured AI instructions and prompts
- **Session Contexts** - Save and restore work sessions
- **Sprint Management** - Built-in sprint planning templates
- **Documentation** - Auto-generated docs folder structure
- **License Management** - Automatic MIT license creation
- **Configuration** - Persistent config in ~/.jcscripts
- **GitHub Integration** - Automatic repository creation via gh CLI
- **Project Refactoring** - Add structure to existing projects
- **Project Extraction** - Restore projects from GitHub
- **Project Abandonment** - Safe project removal with backup (hidden feature)

---

## Prerequisites

### Required Tools

- **git** - Version control
- **gh** (GitHub CLI) - Repository management
- **pnpm** (for monorepo projects) - Package manager
- **Bash** 4.0+ - Shell environment

### GitHub Authentication

```bash
# Authenticate GitHub CLI
gh auth login
```

### Install Prerequisites

```bash
# Install GitHub CLI (Ubuntu/Debian)
curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg | sudo dd of=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg
echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list > /dev/null
sudo apt update
sudo apt install gh

# Install pnpm
npm install -g pnpm

# Or via curl
curl -fsSL https://get.pnpm.io/install.sh | sh -
```

---

## Installation

Part of the JC Scripts Collection:

```bash
./installscripts
```

