## Configuration

### Initial Configuration

On first run, the script prompts for configuration:

```bash
gitproject --config
```

**You'll be asked for:**
- GitHub organization name (for private repos)
- GitHub username (for public repos)
- Full name (for commits/licenses)
- Email (optional)

### Configuration File

Stored in `~/.jcscripts`:

```bash
# JC Scripts Configuration File
DEFAULT_PRIVATE_ORG="YourOrganization"
DEFAULT_PUBLIC_USER="yourusername"
DEFAULT_AUTHOR_NAME="Your Full Name"
DEFAULT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="your.email@example.com"
```

### Updating Configuration

```bash
# Interactive configuration management
gitproject --config

# Or edit manually
vi ~/.jcscripts
```

