## Troubleshooting

### Issue: "GitHub CLI is not authenticated"

**Cause:** `gh` not logged in

**Solution:**
```bash
gh auth login
# Follow prompts to authenticate
```

### Issue: "Repository already exists"

**Cause:** GitHub repository name conflict

**Solution:**
```bash
# Delete existing repo
gh repo delete org/project --yes

# Or use different name
gitproject MyApp2
```

### Issue: "Failed to create public repository"

**Cause:** Insufficient GitHub permissions or quota

**Solution:**
```bash
# Check permissions
gh auth status

# Or create private-only
gitproject MyApp -p
```

### Issue: "pnpm not found"

**Cause:** pnpm not installed (only needed for monorepo)

**Solution:**
```bash
# Install pnpm
npm install -g pnpm

# Or skip monorepo
gitproject MyApp --no-public
```

---

## Technical Details

### Project Structure

```
ProjectName/
├── .git/                          # Private repo git
├── .gitignore                     # Main gitignore
├── .gitproject.conf               # Project configuration
├── README.md                      # Private README
├── LICENSE                        # MIT License
├── activity/                      # Activity tracking (private)
│   ├── status/                   # Session management
│   ├── vibe/                     # AI instructions
│   ├── planning/                 # Plans and roadmaps
│   ├── snapshots/                # Git snapshots
│   ├── sprints/                  # Sprint docs
│   └── templates/                # Doc templates
├── docs/                         # Documentation
└── public/                       # Public repository
    ├── .git/                     # Public repo git
    ├── README.md                 # Public README
    ├── LICENSE                   # Public MIT License
    ├── package.json              # Root package
    ├── pnpm-workspace.yaml       # Workspace config
    ├── api/                      # API component
    ├── frontend/                 # Frontend component
    ├── android/                  # Android component
    └── ios/                      # iOS component
```

### Configuration File Format

`.gitproject.conf`:

```bash
PROJECT_NAME="ProjectName"
PROJECT_TYPE="monorepo"
USE_MONOREPO="true"
PACKAGE_MANAGER="pnpm"

PRIVATE_ORG="Organization"
PRIVATE_REPO="ProjectName"
PRIVATE_REMOTE="git@github.com:Organization/ProjectName.git"

PUBLIC_USER="username"
PUBLIC_REPO="public"
PUBLIC_REMOTE="git@github.com:username/public.git"
PUBLIC_DIR="public"

AUTHOR_NAME="Your Name"
AUTHOR_EMAIL="your.email@example.com"

CREATED_DATE="2025-11-22"
```

