## Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites

**GitProject** is part of the [JC Scripts Collection](https://github.com/Ingasti/jcscripts). For the best experience, install the entire collection which includes all dependencies and utilities.

#### Recommended: Install Full JC Scripts Collection

Follow the [JC Scripts installation guide](https://github.com/Ingasti/jcscripts#getting-started) which will:
- Clone the repository to `~/.scripts`
- Install all required tools (`git`, `gh`, `colorfunctions`, etc.)
- Set up your PATH automatically
- Make all scripts executable

Quick installation:

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Ingasti/jcscripts.git ~/.scripts

# Install prerequisites (git, gh, binutils, etc.)
cd ~/.scripts && ./installextras

# Setup the repository (extract scripts, configure PATH)
./installscripts

# Reload your shell
source ~/.bashrc
```

#### Alternative: Standalone Installation

If you prefer to use `gitproject` standalone (not recommended):

1. **Git** - Version control system
   ```bash
   git --version
   ```

2. **GitHub CLI** - Repository management
   ```bash
   gh --version
   ```

3. **GitHub Authentication**
   ```bash
   gh auth login
   ```

4. **GitHub CLI Scopes** (for advanced features)
   ```bash
   # Required for repository deletion (abandon/extract operations)
   gh auth refresh -h github.com -s delete_repo
   ```

5. **Copy the script and dependencies:**
   ```bash
   # Ensure ~/.scripts directory exists
   mkdir -p ~/.scripts
   
   # Copy gitproject script
   cp gitproject ~/.scripts/
   chmod +x ~/.scripts/gitproject
   
   # Copy colorfunctions library (required dependency)
   cp colorfunctions ~/.scripts/
   ```

6. **Ensure `~/.scripts` is in your PATH:**
   ```bash
   # Add to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.profile
   export PATH="$HOME/.scripts:$PATH"
   
   # Reload shell
   source ~/.bashrc
   ```

> **Note:** When installed as part of JC Scripts Collection, all dependencies and PATH configuration are handled automatically by the `installscripts` setup script.

