## Configuration

### Initial Setup

On first run, the script will prompt for configuration:

```bash
gitproject MyFirstProject
```

You'll be asked for:
- **GitHub Organization** (for private repos)
- **GitHub Username** (for public repos)
- **Full Name** (for commits and licenses)
- **Email** (optional)

Configuration is saved to `~/.jcscripts`.

### Managing Configuration

View and update configuration:

```bash
gitproject --config
```

This opens an interactive menu to:
- View current settings
- Update any value (press Enter to keep current)
- Save changes to `~/.jcscripts`

### Configuration File Location

```
~/.jcscripts
```

Contains:
```bash
# JC Scripts Configuration File
DEFAULT_PRIVATE_ORG="YourOrganization"
DEFAULT_PUBLIC_USER="yourusername"
DEFAULT_AUTHOR_NAME="Your Full Name"
DEFAULT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="your.email@example.com"
```

