## Basic Usage

### Create a New Project

**Simplest form:**
```bash
gitproject MyApp
```

**With description:**
```bash
gitproject MyApp -d "My awesome application"
```

**Custom components:**
```bash
gitproject MyApp --components api,frontend,backend,shared
```

**Private repository only:**
```bash
gitproject MyApp -p
```

### What Gets Created

```
MyAppProj/                           # Private repository
├── .git/
├── .gitignore
├── .gitproject.conf                 # Project configuration
├── README.md
├── LICENSE
├── activity/                        # Activity tracking
│   ├── status/                      # Session contexts
│   ├── vibe/                        # AI instructions & prompts
│   ├── planning/                    # Planning documents
│   ├── snapshots/                   # Historical tracking
│   ├── sprints/                     # Sprint documentation
│   └── templates/                   # Reusable templates
├── docs/                            # Project documentation
└── MyApp/                           # Public repository (monorepo)
    ├── .git/
    ├── README.md
    ├── LICENSE
    ├── package.json
    ├── pnpm-workspace.yaml
    ├── api/
    ├── frontend/
    ├── android/
    └── ios/
```

### GitHub Repositories Created

1. **Private:** `git@github.com:YourOrg/MyAppProj.git`
2. **Public:** `git@github.com:yourusername/MyApp.git`

