## Command Reference

### Standard Options

```bash
gitproject <project-name> [options]
```

#### Required Arguments

- `<project-name>` - Name of the project to create

#### Options

| Option | Description | Default |
|--------|-------------|---------|
| `-t, --type <type>` | Project type (monorepo, docs, script) | monorepo |
| `-m, --monorepo` | Create monorepo structure | enabled |
| `--components <list>` | Comma-separated component list | api,frontend,android,ios |
| `-p, --private` | Create only private repository | disabled |
| `-o, --org <org>` | Organization name for private repo | from config |
| `-u, --user <user>` | Username for public repo | from config |
| `--no-public` | Skip public repository creation | disabled |
| `--no-activity` | Skip activity folder creation | disabled |
| `-d, --description <desc>` | Project description | "{project-name} project" |
| `-r, --refactor` | Refactor existing project | - |
| `-c, --config` | Manage configuration | - |
| `-h, --help` | Show help message | - |
| `-v, --version` | Show script version | - |

### Examples

**Monorepo with custom components:**
```bash
gitproject EcommerceApp \
  --components api,frontend,admin,mobile \
  -d "Full-stack ecommerce platform"
```

**Documentation-only project:**
```bash
gitproject TechDocs \
  --type docs \
  --no-public \
  -d "Technical documentation repository"
```

**Private repository only:**
```bash
gitproject InternalTool \
  -p \
  -d "Internal company tool"
```

**Override organization/user:**
```bash
gitproject ClientProject \
  -o ClientOrganization \
  -u clientusername \
  -d "Client project delivery"
```

