## Appendix

### Useful Commands for Maintenance

```bash
# Count total scripts
find /home/jcgarcia/.scripts -maxdepth 1 -type f -executable | wc -l

# Find scripts without version info
find /home/jcgarcia/.scripts -maxdepth 1 -type f -executable -exec grep -L "Version:" {} \;

# Find scripts with DEBUG statements
grep -r "DEBUG" /home/jcgarcia/.scripts --include="*.sh" --include="*" --exclude-dir=versions

# Check for shellcheck issues
find /home/jcgarcia/.scripts -maxdepth 1 -type f -executable ! -name "*.*" -exec shellcheck {} \;

# List all sourced files
grep -r "source " /home/jcgarcia/.scripts --include="*.sh" --include="*" | grep -v versions

# Find hardcoded paths
grep -r "/home/jcgarcia" /home/jcgarcia/.scripts --include="*.sh" --include="*" --exclude-dir=versions
```

